(16, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MATHS CUE (4-6)', '<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 1.0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">NUMBER:</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 94.3396%;\" border=\"0\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 49.7062%;\"><col style=\"width: 50.2938%;\"></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 1in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Plato said, \"God ever geometrizes\". Jacobi changed this to, \"God is an arithmetician\". Then came Kronecker and fashioned the memorable expression,&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-left: 1in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">&ldquo;God created the natural numbers and all the rest is the work of man&rdquo;&mdash;Felix Klein </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left: 1in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">We begin with &rsquo;1&rsquo;; 1 and 1 together is 2; 2 and 1 together makes 3, and so on are numbers formed.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left: 1in;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 1in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">Note</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">: Our present number system is due to the Indians, who discovered zero and the nine digits from 1 to 9. The discovery of zero by the Indian is considered as the most remarkable invention in the History of Civilization, without it Mathematics, nay Civilizations, could have progressed no further. The Indian Mathematicians are also credited for the discovery of negative numbers. And the most important discovery by them were Algebra (See# 31) and Introductory Calculus (See# ).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 1in;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 1.0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">5.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">NUMERATION:</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 95.2275%;\" border=\"0\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 53.3217%;\"><col style=\"width: 46.7949%;\"></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-left: 1.0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">123 is a number in figures.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left: 1.0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">We read it as &ldquo;One hundred and twenty three&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left: 1.0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">To read a number given in figures is <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Numeration</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 1.0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">6.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif;\">NOTATION/NUMERAL:</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 96.7814%;\" border=\"0\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 50%;\"><col style=\"width: 50%;\"></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Two thousand four hundred. We symbolized the above number as 2400. This process of writing a numbers in figures is &ldquo;Notation&rdquo;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
