(18, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Amount', '<p><strong>41. AMOUNT:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.667%; height: 205.906px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 68%;\"><col style=\"width: 32%;\"></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 205.906px;\">\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; In the above sum (at #39),</span><br><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Amount at the end of 3 years</span><br><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = Principal + Interest</span><br><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Amount = Tk. 5000 + Tk. 900 =</span><br><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In general, Amount, <strong>A = P+ I</strong>, where, <strong>P</strong> is the principal and I is the interest</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>42. RATE OF INTEREST:</strong></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In the sum (at # 39), Rate of Interest = 6% per annum, also, written as 6% p.a. That<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; is, interest or profit earned in 1 (one) year on Tk. 100 is Tk. 6.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; In general, rate of interest is denoted by <strong>&ldquo;R% per annum&rdquo;</strong>, in brief <strong>R% p.a. </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>43. TIME:&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></p>\r\n<p>Time is the period for which the principal is retained in the bank. In the sum (at # 39),<br><strong>Time = </strong>3 years<br>In general, <strong>T</strong> denotes the time; some authors denote time by <strong>&lsquo;n&rsquo;.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>44. RATIO:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\"></strong></p>\r\n<p>The age of a mother is 30 years and her daughter\'s age is 30 months. Ratio helps to<br>compare, their ages.<br>The ratio of the daughter\'s age to her mother\'s age is given by 30 months: 30 years</p>\r\n<p><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;30 months<br>= &mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&nbsp; &nbsp;[lyear=12 months]<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;30x12months&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>=1/12 =1:12 <strong>[To read as &ldquo;one is to twelve&rdquo;]</strong></p>\r\n<p><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
